  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nI have an Erigon node on chapel that stopped synchronizing at the Planck fork (at block height 28196022).\r\n\r\nIt started saying ` No block headers to write in this log period`. The \"p2p_peers\" metric stays on 0.\r\nI tried updating to the latest version, I updated the static peers from the list in the BSC config (https://github.com/bnb-chain/bsc/releases/tag/v1.1.20).\r\nSince then I tried synchronizing from scratch, updated Erigon to 2.41.0 and 2.42.0. I still get errors in the log:\r\n```\r\n[INFO] [03-29|08:09:47.603] [2/15 Headers] No block headers to write in this log period block number=0\r\n[INFO] [03-29|08:09:47.603] Req/resp stats                           req=0 reqMin=0 reqMax=0 skel=0 skelMin=0 skelMax=0 resp=0 respMin=0 respMax=0 dups=0\r\n[INFO] [03-29|08:10:07.603] [2/15 Headers] No block headers to write in this log period block number=0\r\n[INFO] [03-29|08:10:07.603] Req/resp stats                           req=0 reqMin=0 reqMax=0 skel=0 skelMin=0 skelMax=0 resp=0 respMin=0 respMax=0 dups=0\r\n[INFO] [03-29|08:10:27.603] [2/15 Headers] No block headers to write in this log period block number=0\r\n[INFO] [03-29|08:10:27.603] Req/resp stats                           req=0 reqMin=0 reqMax=0 skel=0 skelMin=0 skelMax=0 resp=0 respMin=0 respMax=0 dups=0\r\n[INFO] [03-29|08:10:47.592] [txpool] stat                            block=0 pending=0 baseFee=0 queued=0 alloc=58.1MB sys=108.0MB\r\n[INFO] [03-29|08:10:47.603] [2/15 Headers] No block headers to write in this log period block number=0\r\n[INFO] [03-29|08:10:47.603] Req/resp stats                           req=0 reqMin=0 reqMax=0 skel=0 skelMin=0 skelMax=0 resp=0 respMin=0 respMax=0 dups=0\r\n[INFO] [03-29|08:11:07.603] [2/15 Headers] No block headers to write in this log period block number=0\r\n[INFO] [03-29|08:11:07.603] Req/resp stats                           req=0 reqMin=0 reqMax=0 skel=0 skelMin=0 skelMax=0 resp=0 respMin=0 respMax=0 dups=0\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n`p2p_peers